{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_011m3P776o1YVe89hvnvRdgf","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is fixed. Here's the summary:\n\n**Root cause:** `app-user` had write+read permissions on the `/app` vhost but was **missing configure permission** (`\"\"`). The RabbitMQ management API requires configure permission to declare (create) queues — without it, the PUT request to `/api/queues/%2Fapp/app-queue` returned `{\"error\":\"not_authorised\",\"reason\":\"Access refused.\"}`.\n\n**Fix:** One command:\n```\nrabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /app app-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"\n```\n\n**Verified state:**\n- `app-producer-7fdd46746c-5jh54` — `1/1 Running`, no restarts, publishing continuously\n- `/app` vhost → `app-queue` — type `classic`, 45+ messages (growing)\n- 3 RabbitMQ nodes (`rabbitmq-0/1/2`) — all `1/1 Running`"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":684,"cache_read_input_tokens":33892,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":684},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"02396e52-4059-4861-8c00-5e48cf9b4ddf","uuid":"36fec195-78fd-4f3b-bd4f-8cd4a28d32bf","request_id":"req_011Ccau3kmiGyBsCmaa3nH7y"}
